  "notes": "The 1GR-FE is Toyota's modern 4.0L V6, introduced in 2002 and used across a wide range of truck-based platforms through the 2020s. All-aluminum construction makes it significantly lighter than the iron-block 1FZ-FE it often replaces in swap builds. Features dual VVT-i (Dual Variable Valve Timing with intelligence) on later variants. Compression ratio is 10.0:1 on most applications. A popular and relatively plug-and-play swap into the 80-series Land Cruiser, though it requires fabricated engine mounts, a custom crossmember, and a standalone or adapted ECU. The power-to-weight improvement over the 1FZ-FE is meaningful in off-road applications. Later generations (post-2009) feature improved VVT-i mapping.",
